# Java tests (required)

Full spec: [ai-kit/BACKEND_TEST_CONVENTIONS.md](../../ai-kit/BACKEND_TEST_CONVENTIONS.md)

## Hard rules

1. Read the doc above before editing `service/src/test/**`.
2. **Behavior-first**: organize by observable outcome/condition (`should ... when ...`). Do not require one `@Nested` per source method; at most one `@Nested` level, only for shared setup or a single behavior slice.
3. **Test only classes with logic** (`*Handler`, branching `*Service`, controllers with validation). Do not test models, mappers, or branchless config services.
4. **Single-entry Handler** (only `handle`): `@Test` on the outer class; no `@Nested`; prefer concise BDD `@DisplayName("should ... when ...")`; method names `shouldReturn{Outcome}When{Condition}`.
5. **Service tests**: exercise branching through service API and observable outcomes; flat by default; optional one `@Nested` when setup is shared.
6. **API boundary / Controllers (MockMvc)**: group by behavior, not by controller method name; flat tests inside any group; `testHelper.request(...)`.
7. **Request validation coverage**: for request DTO constraints (e.g. `@NotNull`, `@Size(min/max)`, `@Pattern`), include invalid boundary cases per constrained field in API boundary tests; do not place request validation cases in handler tests.
8. **Parameterized invalid cases**: prefer `@ParameterizedTest` + `@MethodSource` with `InvalidRequestCase` (expected `ErrorCode`, request, description); place the source right above the test.
9. **Authorization checks**: add authorization checks after request validation cases.
10. **Success cases**: one happy-path success per behavior under test; move extra business branches to handler or service tests.
11. Extend `SpringBootIntegrationTests`; call `testHelper.clearAll()` in `@BeforeEach`.
12. Test data: `AuthData` / `UserData` + `TestConst.UID_*`; encode passwords with `PasswordEncoder.encode`.
13. Use AssertJ; handler business logic via `@Autowired Handler` + `handle(...)`; HTTP validation via MockMvc.
14. **`@MockitoSpyBean` only on `SpringBootIntegrationTests`**; never on subclasses.
15. Section comments in each `@Test`: `// Given`, `// When`, `// Then` (or `// When / Then`).
16. Keep test wording in BDD style and prefer short form: `should ... when ...` for `@DisplayName`.
17. Keep `@DisplayName` text lowercase at the start (for example: `should return BAD_TOKEN when token is malformed`).
18. Run from repo root: `./gradlew :service:test`.

## Handler template (single `handle`)

```java
@DisplayName("FooHandler")
class FooHandlerTest extends SpringBootIntegrationTests {

  @Autowired TestHelper testHelper;
  @Autowired FooHandler fooHandler;

  @BeforeEach
  void setup() {
    testHelper.clearAll();
  }

  @Test
  @DisplayName("should throw ApiException when input is invalid")
  void shouldThrowApiExceptionWhenInputIsInvalid() {
    // Given
    // When / Then
    assertThatThrownBy(() -> fooHandler.handle(request)).isInstanceOf(ApiException.class);
  }
}
```
